    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>OSSINING: OFFICERS CLEARED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By ELSA BRENNER</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Federal investigation clears Ossining Police Officers Raymond DeBenedictis, Richard Damiano and Daniel Slater of criminal wrongdoing in July 1998 shooting death of 24-year-old black man, Chris Malone (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A federal investigation has exonerated three white Ossining police officers in the July 1998 shooting death of Chris Malone, a 24-year-old black man. The investigation cleared the officers, Raymond DeBenedictis, Richard Damiano and Daniel Slater, of criminal wrongdoing. After reports that Mr. Malone had fired a gun, the officers chased and caught him, shooting him after the suspect pointed a handgun at them. Federal officials said the investigation failed to establish beyond a reasonable doubt that the officers had used unreasonable force.</p>
        <p>ELSA BRENNER</p>
      </block>
